This paper deals with image classification and learning discriminative parts from labeled training images. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves optimization techniques and learning algorithms, which are common in sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses natural language processing and scene recognition, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
